article.headline: Maryland 76, Elon 50
article.story: COLLEGE PARK, Md. -- Greivis Vasquez scored 10 of his 17 points during a 21-2 second-half run that enabled Maryland to pull away to its sixth straight win, 76-50 over Elon on Tuesday night. The Terrapins (10-2) let a 17-point lead shrink to 40-33 before Vasquez went to work. The junior guard sank three shots from 3-point range during the surge and had two of his season-high eight assists. Landon Milbourne scored 14 and David Neal had nine points and a career-best 10 rebounds for Maryland, now 8-0 at home. TJ Douglas led Elon (4-5) with 14 points and Ola Atoyebi snared 11 rebounds. Neal scored the first two baskets of the second half to put Maryland up 40-23. Elon then rattled off 10 straight points while holding the Terrapins scoreless for more than four minutes. Neal ended the drought with a 3-pointer, then Vasquez drilled two from long range.
